observations.recommendation:
We also recommended that henceforth, the following have to be undertaken or strictly observed:
- that the Bids and Awards Committee ensure that procurement of services for garbage hauling and disposal be made thru public bidding; 
- that the Bids and Awards Committee ensure that the contractor is eligible to undertake the contract for garbage hauling and disposal by strictly adhering to the relevant provisions of Republic Act 9184; 
- that the Municipal Mayor see to it that the contract of services entered into by and between the Municipal Government clearly defined the premises and considerations necessary in the garbage collection and disposal or conform to the items specified in bidding documents/scope of work; and 
- that the Municipal Accountant see to it that all the necessary supporting documents to prove the validity of claims for services rendered are attached to the disbursement vouchers.

We recommended that the City Accountant undertake the following:
reconcile the Real Property Tax Receivables and Special Education Tax Receivables with the Records of Real Property Tax Delinquencies maintained by the Municipal Treasurer’s Office;
coordinate with the Municipal Treasurer’s Office to obtain the desired information on the Real Property Tax Receivables and Special Education Tax Receivables such as the name of taxpayers, amount and period of delinquencies, and other related information;
maintain and update regularly the subsidiary ledgers.

We recommended that the Municipal Accountant ensure the following:
no additional cash advance is granted prior to settlement of the previous advances;
as much as possible, payments should be made directly to the suppliers of goods and/or associations;
breakdown of the estimated expenses  for  projects/activities  to  be undertaken are attached to the disbursement vouchers;
no cash advance is granted for project to be implemented in the ensuing year; and
all cash advances are fully liquidated at the end of the year.

the Municipal Budget Officer, Accountant and Treasurer exercise diligence, prudence and proper control in the disposition of government funds. They should limit the expenditures within the total income realized during the year to avoid incurrence of cash overdraft.  They should likewise find ways to cover the cash deficit with the collections in the ensuing year;
the Municipal Budget Officer ensure that all expenditures are covered with valid appropriations;
the Municipal Treasurer settle immediately the Due from General Fund in the Trust Fund books to address the cash deficit in the latter; and
the Municipal Treasurer and Accountant ensure that funds received for specific purpose is available and spent only for the purpose for which the trust was created or the funds received.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor ensure/ direct the following:
immediate delivery of  the  medicines  and  drugs  amounting  to P708,500.00 and to impose liquidated damages for the delay in the delivery;
expedite the construction of the school clinics within the terms and conditions of the contract;
identify government lot for the  construction  of  the  Noveleta  Mini  Fish  Port  and/or  coordinate  with  the   Department   of Agriculture- Bureau of Fisheries and Aquatic  Resources  for  the  realignment of fund to another related project, if possible.;
that in the ensuing BuB projects to  be  requested  for  funding from the National Government, the Municipality should look into feasible infrastructure projects with available sites/locations; and
completion/implementation of the BuB projects be within the timeframe set by the Municipality.

We recommended that the  Municipal Mayor direct the Municipal Budget Officer, Accountant and  Treasurer to:

1.	exercise utmost diligence in the disposition of government funds;
2.	limit expenses to actual income received;
3.	make sure that obligations incurred are always supported by funds available for such purpose/s;
4.	ensure that inter-agency payables and other current liabilities that are considered as trust receipts should be utilized only for the specific purpose for which these were created or received; and
5.	remit to the concerned government agencies the funds collected by the Municipality in their behalf within the reglementary period to avoid the occurrence of cash deficit.
